data: "Rahim Kay Joshilay vs Faakhir Kay Janbaaz"

In the 2nd episode of this show, the 1st encounter of this show between Rahim Shah & his team Rahim Kay Joshilay went headon against Faakhir & his team Faakhir Kay Janbaaz. Anoushey Ashraf joined as the 2nd host of this show. Balloting & the selection of teams were shown at the start. Then came the both teams. 1st Segment: Ikkay Pe Ikka: Faakhir won the toss and decided that his team will perform 1st. Raheel from Faakhir's team performed in the first segment Ikkay Pe Ikka. In his 1st performance he performed "Naina Thug Lein Ge (Rahat Fateh Ali Khan)". Points Awarded: Audience: 8, Judges: Rameez: 7, Fariha 7, Shiraz 8, Haroon 8.5 (Judges Average: 7.6) Then Shaz Khan peformed "Agar Tum Na Hotey (Kishor Kumar & Lata)" from the Joshilay's side and scored: Audience: 8.4, Judges: Rameez 7, Fariha 7, Shiraz 9, Haroon (Judges Average: 8) Then Raheel came on to the stage to perform his 2nd soong for the 1st segment and he performed "Daman Lagiyan Moula (Abida Parveen)" and scored: Audience: 7.6, Judges: Rameez 7.5, Fariha 7.5, Shiraz 7, Haroon 7.5(Judges Average: 7.3) After this Shaz Khan came for his 2nd performance "Koi Jab Tumhara Hriday Tod De (Mukesh)" Audience: 8.3, Judges: Rameez 7.8, Fariha 7.5, Shiraz 9, Haroon 9(Judges Average:8.3) Total Score: Rahim Kay Joshilay: 32 Faakhir Kay Janbaaz: 30.5 2nd Segment: Aar Ya Paar: In this duet round Rose Merry from Faakhir's Janbaaz to perform alongside Ali Asad from Rahim's Joshilay & they performed "Zoobi Doobi (Sonu Nigam & Shreya Ghoshal)". Performance was a duet but they were judged individually. According to the judges Rose Merry from Faakhir's Janbaaz performed better than Ali Asad from Rahim's Joshilay. And their score are as follows: Rose Merry (Faakhir Kay Janbaaz): Audience: 8.4, Judges: Rameez 7, Fariha 7, Shiraz 7, Haroon 7.5(Judges Average:7.1) Ali Asad (Rahim Kay Joshilay): Audience: 8, Judges: Rameez 6, Fariha 6.5, Shiraz 6, Haroon 6.5(Judges Average:6.3) Total Score after 2nd round: Rahim Kay Joshilay: 32 Faakhir Kay Janbaaz: 30.5 Awaz Ka Jadoo: In this round Rafeh Ali from Faakhir's Janbaaz came on to perform & he performed "Kuch Is Tarha (Atif Aslam)" while Hina from Rahim Kay Joshilay performed "Aaja Sohneya (Shazia Manzoor)." Rafeh Ali (Faakhir Kay Janbaaz): Audience: 7.5, Judges: Rameez 7.5, Fariha 7.5, Shiraz 9, Haroon 9(Judges Average:8.3) Hina (Rahim Kay Joshilay): Audience: 7.4, Judges: Rameez 7, Fariha 7.5, Shiraz 8, Haroon 7(Judges Average:7.4) Total Score after round 3: Rahim Kay Joshilay: 61.7 Faakhir Kay Janbaaz: 61.8 Zarra Hut Kay: Both the team captains performed medleys in this segment along with their entire team while only the audience passed the judgement this time. Songs Performed by Faakhir Kay Janbaaz: 1) Marjawan (Faakhir) - Performed by Faakhir, 2) Akhiyan Udeek Diyan (Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan) - Performed by Rafeh Ali, 3) Afreen Afreen (Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan) - Performed by Rose Merry, 4) Piya Re (Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan) - Raheel, 5) Mera Piya Ghar Aya (Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan) - Performed by Nouman Shafi. Points given by Audience: 8.6 Songs Performed by Rahim Kay Joshilay: 1) Channa Ve Channa (Rahim Shah) - Performed by Rahim Shah, 2) Meri Mehbooba (Kumar Sanu , Alka Yagnik) - Performed by Shaz Khan, 3) Payale Chunmun (Kumar Sanu,Chitra), 4) Dil De Diya Hai (Anand Raaj Anand) - Performed by Ali Asad, 5) Dil Main Ho Tum Aankhon Main Tum (Neha Rajpa, Sanjay Sawant). Points given by Audience: 8.4 Final Score: Rahim Kay Joshilay: 70.1 Faakhir Kay Janbaaz: 70.4 So Faakhir & his team won the vert 1st encounter only by 0.3 difference

"Haroon Kay Matwalay vs Fariha Kay Surilay"

The 2nd encounter of this show was between Haroon Kay Matwalay & Fariha Kay Surilay.It started with the introduction. Fariha Pervez 1st came & performed her Bokata & introduced her team. Haroon performed his song Mehbooba before introducing his team to everyone. After that Haroon won the toss and decided that Fariha Kay Surilay will perform 1st. 1st Segment: Ikkay Pe Ikka: Ali Raza performed from Fariha Pervez's side & sang "Tere Bina (Fuzon)." Points awarded: Audience: 7.6, Judges: Rameez 7, Shiraz 7.5, Faakhir 6, Rahim 9(Judges Average:7.4). Faraz Ali performed "Saanware Torey Bina Jiya Jaye Na (Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan)."Points awarded: Audience: 8.5, Judges: Rameez 8.5, Shiraz 9, Faakhir 9, Rahim 9.9(Judges Average:9.1) Then Ali Raza came for his 2nd performance & performed "Main Tenu Samjhawan Ki (Rahat Fateh Ali Khan)." Points: Audience: 7.9, Judges: Rameez 7.5, Shiraz 8.5, Faakhir 8, Rahim 8(Judges Average:8) And Faraz performed "Bismillah Karan (Nadeem Abbas/Malkoo)."Points: Audience: 8, Judges: Rameez 8, Shiraz 7.5, Faakhir 8, Rahim 6(Judges Average:7.4) Total Score after the 1st round: Haroon Kay Matwalay: 33 Fariha Kay Surilay: 30.9 2nd Segment: Aar Ya Paar: Amjad Warsi from Fariha Kay Surilay performed Pehla Nasha Pehla Khumar (Udit Narayan, Sadhana Sargam) alongside Anmol from Haroon Kay Matwalay. Amjad Warsi (Fariha Kay Surilay): Audience: 6.6, Judges: Rameez 4, Shiraz 4, Faakhir 4, Rahim 6 (Judges Average:4.5). Anmol (Haroon Kay Matwalay): Audience: 6.6, Judges: Rameez 5, Shiraz 3, Faakhir 3, Rahim 2 (Judges Average:3.3) Total Score after 2nd round: Haroon Kay Matwalay: 42.9 Fariha Kay Surilay: 42 Awaz Ka Jadoo: Waqas Azeem performed from Fariha's side while Wajeeh Uddin performed from Haroon's side. Citation: For the skillful juxtaposing and interweaving of two parallel destinies, the personal and the political; for the setting these against the decadent splendor of the court of Avadh, recreated with a sense of great pictorial beauty and musical charm; for presenting vividly the clash of two cultures, irreconcilable in their distinctive views of the world; for performances of remarkable depth and range, true to the style and flavor of the period.

data: The fine St John's Gate is built into the church under its spire; the line of the walls is walkable.

Originally built by the Romans in the 3rd century and retained by the Anglo-Saxons, the walls were rebuilt in the late 14th century owing to fears of a French invasion and feature early gunports. Over half of the original circuit, with 17 of 24 original towers, survives.

First recorded in 1111, the walls were mi (km) long, with an average height of ft (m) and five town gates. Sections collapsed in the 18th century, and many stones were then re-used as building material. The last large section was demolished in 1901.

With its walls nearly mi (km) around and ft (m) high, with 32 towers and 12 gatehouses, repaired during the 1640s, Coventry was described as being the best-defended city in England outside London. Introduction: the building of the wall, Coventry's City Wall and Gates, retrieved 1 October 2008.

Built of brick in the 14th century, with four main gates and up to 30 towers, the walls were maintained until the early 1700s. They were demolished during the building of the docks, beginning in the 1770s.
Only the Monnow Bridge gate survives
Originally formed a circuit wall with four gatehouses, none of which survive. The fortified Monnow bridge still remains, the only surviving medieval bridge gate in the UK.
Originally constructed of earth and timber, probably in the late 14th century,
The Roman town of Calleva Atrebatum was abandoned around the 5th or 6th century. Much of the walls survive, the area within them largely farmland.
Remains include the Baste Walls, South Street and the Eastgate, which was greatly altered in the 19th century.
The site of the Roman town of Verulamium was abandoned when the later settlement of St. Albans was established nearby.

data: Welcome to Babylonia, home of Lena, Mahad and their mother Mila. A peaceful haven in the tyranny of the Sphere, the family lives happily, but with a secret. Seijins (humans with telekinetic powers) are the most wanted people in Skyland, something Mila knows only too well, as both she and her daughter belong to this select group. The children are unaware of their Mother's secret until an incident at their home exposes both Mila and Lena and they are forced to flee. Knowing the Sphere will hunt them down; Mila sends her children away and stays behind to be captured by the Sphere. Lena and Mahad are sent away in a stolen enemy ship when suddenly they find themselves confronted by the Pirates. The children are taken in by the band of pirates and learn even more of their parents past. They are escorted to their father's last known secret headquarters only to find his famous Hyperion ship—seemingly waiting for Mahad to inherit. Unfortunately, they are intercepted by the evil Diwan, minion to Sphere leader Oslo and they are forced to battle their way out. They rejoin the pirates who invite the children to live in Puerto Angel where they will continue the fight to find their mother and defeat the evil Sphere. And so, the adventure begins.

An old friend of the Vector's sends news to Puerto Angel - he may have a lead on Lena and Mahad's mother. They travel to Ningxia, a Chinese block, where they find a Sphere invasion in progress and are captured. In jail, they are introduced to the Vector's friend, Master Hailong Zalo, also a powerful Seijin. In a daring escape, Zalo psychically bonds with Lena to give her a telepathic message from her mother, in turn giving her enough power to defeat the invasion and escape with Mahad.

Puerto Angel suffers through a severe drought that ends up dangerously dehydrating Lena. The pirates investigate a remote block of ice that the Vector believes will supply them with much needed water. Upon arriving, they find that the Sphere has struck first, the pirates board the deserted drilling station in hopes of finding some water the Sphere may have left behind. There, they battle the Mogura, a huge spider-like robot that has turned from a simple tool into a deadly threat to any human that confronts it. Thankfully, the pirates (including a weak Lena) manage to fight the creature off, collect the vast water supply left behind and save the people of Puerto Angel.

With all of her strength, she harnesses the power of the lightning to melt the ice block allowing Mahad and Dahlia to escape safely in the Hyperion.

He uses Dahlia to attack Puerto Angel's water storage tank, and pin the blame on Lena. Mahad is bewildered and more than a little angry at the change in Dahlia, who is really trying to fight her way free of Oslo's control. Lena is also feeling the effects of the solar phenomenon, and is uncertain of her own innocence. She turns to the Vector for help, and together they discover that Oslo is responsible. Lena uses her powers to get into Dahlia's head, and although she isn't strong enough to fight against Oslo, she convinces Dahlia that no one should be able to boss her around in her own body.
